 {"id":"franken_networkx-23y1","title":"parity: MultiGraph and MultiDiGraph EdgeView should satisfy keyed mapping protocol","description":"MultiGraph.edges and MultiDiGraph.edges currently fail NetworkX's keyed EdgeView mapping contract. In FrankenNetworkX, G.edges has no get((u, v, k), default) helper and dict(G.edges) silently produces {'a': 'b'} on a single keyed edge instead of the upstream {('a', 'b', 'k1'): {'weight': 3}} mapping. Match the upstream multigraph EdgeView mapping contract, including keyed get() behavior and dict(...) conversion.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:40:42.335525348Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T09:40:42.335525348Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
